---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'Architecture Marketing Resources | IPQmedia';
const description =
  'Practical guides on lead generation, paid ads, and client acquisition for US architecture firms, from the team that builds these systems for a living.';
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Architecture marketing, without the guesswork</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Most firms still win work the slow way: referrals, repeat clients, and hoping
    the phone rings. This is the library for the firms that want a system instead.
    Real playbooks on getting found, getting leads, and turning them into signed
    high-end projects.
  </p>

  <p>
    We run client acquisition for US architecture firms every day. These guides are
    the same thinking we use when we build it for a client, written so you can act on
    it whether you hire help or do it yourself.
  </p>

  <h2>Start here</h2>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <a class="card" href="/architecture-marketing">
      <h3>Architecture marketing: the full picture →</h3>
      <p>The map for everything below. What marketing for a firm actually is, why the work doesn't market itself, and the four-part system that wins residential and commercial projects on purpose.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card" href="/lead-generation-for-architects">
      <h3>Lead generation for architects →</h3>
      <p>How firms build a predictable pipeline of qualified project enquiries, and what actually moves the needle versus what wastes budget.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card" href="/meta-ads-for-architects">
      <h3>Meta ads for architects →</h3>
      <p>Why "my clients aren't on Facebook" is the most expensive assumption in the business, and how Meta ads actually win high-end projects.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card" href="/seo-for-architects">
      <h3>SEO for architects →</h3>
      <p>The marketing that keeps working after you stop paying. How firms rank on Google for the searches that bring real projects, the three levers that move rankings, and how long it honestly takes.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card" href="/marketing-for-residential-architects">
      <h3>Marketing for residential architects →</h3>
      <p>Your best client doesn't know they're allowed to hire you yet. How to reach homeowners early, earn their trust, and win the project of their life.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card" href="/marketing-for-commercial-architects">
      <h3>Marketing for commercial architects →</h3>
      <p>Commercial work is won on a shortlist you were never told about. How to get found, get shortlisted, and become the safe, obvious choice.</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h2>Who this is for</h2>
  <p>
    Principals and partners at US architecture firms who want more of the right
    projects and less dependence on word of mouth. If that is you, these guides will
    save you months of trial and error.
  </p>

  <p>Want the system built for you instead of by you?</p>
  <a class="cta-block" href="https://ipqmedia.com/book-a-call">Book a call with IPQmedia</a>
</Base>
